data.title: Mastercard's strong quarter with $8.60 billion net revenue, up 17% YoY, faces potential softening due to Capital One roll-off.
data.description: Mastercard Incorporated (NYSE: MA) had a strong quarter with resilient consumer spending and steady global transaction growth. Despite currency shifts and competitive challenges, the company managed to perform well. Although U.S. volumes were briefly affected by portfolio conversions in October, JP Morgan analyst Tien-tsin Huang maintained an Overweight rating on Mastercard with a price target of $685 following the third-quarter fiscal 2025 results. The company reported quarterly net revenues of $8.60 billion, a 17% increase year-over-year and 15% on a neutral currency basis, surpassing the analyst consensus estimate of $8.53 billion. For the fourth quarter, Mastercard anticipates net revenue growth in the high teens, as opposed to the analyst consensus estimate of $8.71 billion. They expressed confidence in the economy citing stable inflation, robust labor markets, and strong financial markets contributing to consumer wealth.
